acceptOwnership().notice: Accept the nomination to be owner.

depositSynths(uint256).notice: depositSynths: Allows users to deposit synths via the approve / transferFrom workflow        if they'd like. You can equally just transfer synths to this contract and it will work        exactly the same way but with one less call (and therefore cheaper transaction fees)

exchangeEtherForSynthetixAtRate(uint256,.notice: Exchange ETH to SNX while insisting on a particular set of rates. This allows a user to        exchange while protecting against frontrunning by the contract owner on the exchange rates.

exchangeEtherForSynthsAtRate(uint256).notice: Exchange ETH to sUSD while insisting on a particular rate. This allows a user to        exchange while protecting against frontrunning by the contract owner on the exchange rate.

exchangeSynthsForSynthetixAtRate(uint256.notice: Exchange sUSD for SNX while insisting on a particular rate. This allows a user to        exchange while protecting against frontrunning by the contract owner on the exchange rate.

initiateSelfDestruct().notice: Begin the self-destruction counter of this contract. Once the delay has elapsed, the contract may be self-destructed.

nominateNewOwner(address).notice: Nominate a new owner of this contract.

pricesAreStale().notice: Check if the prices haven't been updated for longer than the stale period.

selfDestruct().notice: If the self-destruction delay has elapsed, destroy this contract and remit any ether it owns to the beneficiary address.

setFundsWallet(address).notice: Set the funds wallet where ETH raised is held

setMinimumDepositAmount(uint256).notice: Set the minimum deposit amount required to depoist sUSD into the FIFO queue

setOracle(address).notice: Set the Oracle that pushes the synthetix price to this contract

setPaused(bool).notice: Change the paused state of the contract

setPriceStalePeriod(uint256).notice: Set the stale period on the updated price variables

setSelfDestructBeneficiary(address).notice: Set the beneficiary address of this contract.

setSynth(address).notice: Set the Synth contract that the issuance controller uses to issue Synths.

setSynthetix(address).notice: Set the Synthetix contract that the issuance controller uses to issue SNX.

synthetixReceivedForEther(uint256).notice: Calculate how many SNX you will receive if you transfer        an amount of ether.

synthetixReceivedForSynths(uint256).notice: Calculate how many SNX you will receive if you transfer        an amount of synths.

synthsReceivedForEther(uint256).notice: Calculate how many synths you will receive if you transfer        an amount of ether.

terminateSelfDestruct().notice: Terminate and reset the self-destruction timer.

tokenFallback(address,uint256,bytes).notice: Triggers when users send us SNX or sUSD, but the modifier only allows sUSD calls to proceed.

updatePrices(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Access point for the oracle to update the prices of SNX / eth.

withdrawMyDepositedSynths().notice: Allows a user to withdraw all of their previously deposited synths from this contract if needed.        Developer note: We could keep an index of address to deposits to make this operation more efficient        but then all the other operations on the queue become less efficient. It's expected that this        function will be very rarely used, so placing the inefficiency here is intentional. The usual        use case does not involve a withdrawal.

withdrawSynthetix(uint256).notice: Allows the owner to withdraw SNX from this contract if needed.
